				<p><p>Stage and Gazebo are open source 2D and 3D simulators respectively. They are created and maintained by the <a href="http://playerstage.sourceforge.net/">Player project</a>. They are very easy to use and have a lot of pre-built maps and robots. Depending on the experience of your audience you may need to do a bit of the heavy lifting (i.e. building configuration files and the main classes).</p>

<p>They have a couple of additional benefits as well. First, so long as you create your main control code as player plug-ins then they can be easily adapted to real robots. Second, there are a large number of plug-ins already built to work with real hardware. Third, they work with <a href="http://ros.org">ROS</a>.</p>
